title: Act3_FalseHumanInvestigation_N4
---
/// no repeat
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: You actually did it. Are you a Hunter?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I’ve been waiting for the right dispatcher.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: ...Are you a mind reader?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Maybe. I think we’d make a pretty good team.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Huh, I was thinking the same... Oh! Saul! Tobias! Over here!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: Hey, Eve! And, uh, new guy. Don’t think I’ve seen you around before.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Cyrus, he’s a hunter-in-training.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: Who’s training him?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Me. I’m going to be his dispatcher.
 
<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: Not with that equipment, You know memory monsters have been spreading like wildfire through the outskirts lately.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Yeah, yeah, we’re headed to the shop.

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]Eve walks away and Cyrus begins to follow.[/i] TODO

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: Hey kid, let me give you some real hunting training.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: We need to get this job over with Saul, the Ministry’s started docking pay if you’re late.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: The MPS commissions Hunters?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: Only when they need a live Meminiscor. They never tell us why, though. Government secrets.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: Don’t lie to him, Tobias. If he’s going to be a hunter, he should know.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Know what?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: MPS likes to keep things under wraps, but word is they use live monsters for False Human trials.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: It isn’t wise to believe every rumor.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: False Humans are the most evolved tier of memory monsters, right? And have you ever seen two monsters fighting each other on the outskirts?
Saul: Nope, they only go after humans!
Saul: I’d bet the MPS chucks all their false human suspects to the memory monsters. That’s the only way to know for sure.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: And what if their suspicions are wrong?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: It’s a risk you’ve gotta take.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: How are we protecting humanity if we’re putting innocent people at risk?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: I mean, what’s the alternative? Let False Humans run free, start the Assimilation whenever they feel like it?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Tobias>>
Tobias: Ahem- Ignore Saul, this isn’t the first rabbit hole he’s been down. MPS probably just wants a live specimen for research.
Tobias: You better catch up with Eve, it’s not safe out here.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Saul>>
Saul: See you on the next hunt.

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]Cyrus follows Eve’s path.[/i] TODO

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]Wait...last loop, weren’t we ambushed by memory monsters on this path?[/i]
Cyrus: [i] ...Eve![/i]
===


